<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Get Involved · Regenerate Skagit</title>

  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f8f7f4;
      --text: #1f2933;
      --muted: #5f6c7b;
      --accent: #2f855a;
      --card-bg: #f1f3f0;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --border: #e5e7eb;
      --shadow: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
                   "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    main {
      max-width: 42rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    header {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      box-shadow: 0 3px 8px var(--shadow);
      text-align: center;
    }

    header strong {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    h1 { font-size: 2rem; line-height: 1.25; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    h3 { font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

    p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }

    .section { margin-top: 2.5rem; }

    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      box-shadow: 0 3px 8px var(--shadow);
    }

    .featured {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      background: var(--card);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 5px var(--shadow);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .featured strong { font-weight: 600; }

    .details {
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .divider {
      margin: 3rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    footer {
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding-top: 2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: center;
    }

    footer a {
      color: var(--muted);
      text-decoration: none;
      margin: 0 0.5rem;
    }

    @media(min-width:768px){
      main { padding: 3rem 2rem; }
      h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; }
      h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
      h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header>
      <strong>Regenerate Skagit</strong>
      <h1>Three Paths to Get Involved</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        Regeneration is participatory. It begins with attention and grows through relationship.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        You can begin wherever feels natural.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">

      <!-- Path One -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Path One · Learn About Regeneration</h3>
        <p>Regeneration starts with understanding how living systems work — ecologically, socially, and culturally.</p>
        <p>Watch Joe Brewer introduce the deeper patterns behind regenerative design and place-based work.</p>

        <div class="featured">
          <strong>Start here</strong><br>
          Watch the Introduction Video<br>
          Explore the Design School for Regenerating Earth
        </div>

        <div class="details">
          Systems thinking · Watershed awareness · Learning journeys · Global context
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Path Two -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Path Two · Join Our Monthly Gathering</h3>
        <p>Regeneration is not only projects. It is relationships.</p>
        <p>Each month we gather to practice deep listening, shared reflection, and collective sensemaking about what is emerging in the Skagit watershed.</p>

        <div class="featured">
          <strong>Next Gathering</strong><br>
          Monthly Community Listening Circle<br>
          Mount Vernon · Details shared via newsletter
        </div>

        <div class="details">
          Deep listening · Curiosity · Conversation · No preparation required
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Path Three -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Path Three · Map Regeneration in Skagit</h3>
        <p>Regeneration is already happening — in farms, schools, watershed groups, small businesses, and neighborhood initiatives.</p>
        <p>We are building a living map of regenerative efforts across Skagit County.</p>

        <div class="featured">
          <strong>Contribute to the Map</strong><br>
          Share a project, organization, or story of regeneration
        </div>

        <div class="details">
          Local projects · Community initiatives · Ecological restoration · Food systems · Cultural renewal
        </div>
      </div>

    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
      <h2>Start where you are</h2>
      <p>There are no membership requirements and no fixed commitments.</p>
      <p>Some people begin by learning. Others begin by gathering. Some begin by noticing and sharing what is already alive here.</p>
      <p>Regeneration grows through participation, at the pace of relationship.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <p>Rooted in the Skagit watershed, Cascadia.</p>
      <p>
        <a href="#">Contact</a>
        <a href="#">Newsletter</a>
        <a href="#">Instagram</a>
      </p>
    </footer>

  </main>
</body>
</html>
